# gen191 — RATCHETED (was gen187's open gap). Renaming under a DIRECTORY chains F4
# localization into the F5 edit+verify loop: parrot0 first locates the file that
# defines the function (recursively, sandboxed), then renames the identifier in a
# temp copy, compiles to verify, and reports the file relative to the directory —
# the original is never touched.
#expect: pass
#faculty: edit-locate
> rename the function add to plus under tests/code
< Renamed add to plus in fixtures/sample.c (2 occurrences); the result still compiles.
# A rename that collides with an existing definition is caught by the real
# compiler, not guessed — grounded verification (CODE-MASTERY.md §4).
> rename the function add to square under tests/code/fixtures
< Renamed add to square in sample.c (2 occurrences), but the result no longer compiles.
# Honest decline when no file under the directory defines the function.
> rename the function greet to hi under tests/code
< I looked through tests/code but found no file that defines greet.
